data.title: Kris Jenner goes on date night in Paris with Corey Gamble on latest ep of 'The Kardashians'
data.meta_description: Jenner and Gamble, who have a 25-year age gap, reportedly first began dating in August 2014.
data.text:
Kris Jenner is reflecting on her enduring love for Corey Gamble on ‘The Kardashians.’

The latest episode features the longtime couple enjoying a romantic getaway in Paris, where their love story began 10 years ago.

During a luxurious, moonlit dinner overlooking the Eiffel Tower, Kris reminisces about their first date in the City of Lights. She playfully compares the scene to ‘The Bachelorette,’ highlighting the intimacy and child-free atmosphere.

In a confessional, Kris opens up about the initial reservations she had regarding their 25-year age gap. She playfully quotes Corey's response, “Age is just a number. It's a f***ing big number, but it's a number!”

Despite initial doubts, Kris acknowledges their undeniable chemistry and the joy they've shared over nearly a decade together.

Kris and Corey met in Ibiza in 2014 and have been inseparable ever since. While they maintain a private romance, they occasionally share sweet sentiments on social media and even released a family holiday card together in 2022.

Corey has also been a regular on ‘Keeping Up With the Kardashians’ and continues to appear on ‘The Kardashians.’

Kris has consistently praised Corey for his unwavering support both personally and professionally. In a 2021 interview with WSJ. Magazine, she called him an “amazing support system.”

In July 2022, she described him to PEOPLE, “I think Corey is super. He's an amazing guy,” she said, adding, “He's such a great person to bounce things off of. I really love his point of view on things.”

New episodes of ‘The Kardashians’ drop Thursdays at 12 a.m. ET on Hulu.
